Figs 11–13
). Subcapitulum nearly as long as wide ( 69–73 × 69–73 ). Rutellum longer than gena. Hypostomal setae setiform, smooth; a ( 12–20 ) little longer than m ( 8–12 ) and h ( 6–8 ). Setae h inserted towards middle of mentum. Two pairs of adoral setae ( or , 8–12 ) setiform, slightly barbed, curved medio-distally. Palps ( 65– 73 ) with setation 0–2 – 1–3 – 8 (+ 1 ω). Solenidion long, setiform, weakly curved, not fused with acm. Chelicerae ( 73– 82 ) chelate-dentate. Cheliceral setae long, setiform, barbed; cha ( 20–24 ) longer, than chb ( 12–16 ). Trägårdh’s organ poorly visible.

